Bluehost Inc.

1958 South 950 East 
Provo UT 84606 United States
Phone: +1 801-___-____
Fax: +1 801-___-____
http://www.bluehost.com





6
Managers




40
IT employees




$9.2MEST.
IT Budget




Bluehost is a company that provides global Web hosting solutions to a wide variety of clients. It also maintains its own data center and servers.  Bluehost is owned by Endurance International Group.
Bluehost Inc.'s primary IT hub is located with its headquarters in Provo, UT. The IT department also maintains a centralized data center at this location. The facility is spread over 50,000 square feet and contains hundreds of servers. The company… MoreBluehost Inc.'s primary IT hub is located with its headquarters in Provo, UT. The IT department also maintains a centralized data center at this location. The facility is spread over 50,000 square feet and contains hundreds of servers. The company hosts over a million domains. Additionally, Bluehost has two other secondary facilities, one in Provo and the other in Orem, together totaling over 20,000 square feet. The secondary locations do not host client data, but do host employee offices. Technicians work directly from the primary data center. The company does not offer any cloud computing services and has no plans of expanding into that market at this time.

The computer operations team manages server deployment and purchases, as well as data center design and build outs. Additionally, the software team is responsible for programming efforts and shares information security management with the network operations team.

The company offers shared Linux servers to customers. However, they also work with Apache Servers and UNIX. Additionally, EMC Data Domain is the primary data storage tool. Other prominent technologies include Microsoft products, LAMP, Ruby on Rails, WordPress blogging tools and VMware.





